cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper presents a novel key-point detector based on sparse coding, which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method does not rely on pre-designed structures, which suggests a potential contribution to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed detector using datasets, which indicates a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
